    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="864"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-16">December 16,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received December 18—1:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>555. Peiping, south (Nankuan) airfield was subjected Communist artillery fire 9
                    a.m. today whereupon 7 of 8 CNAC and CAT planes on field immediately took off
                    only one remaining presumably for VIPS. Chartered plane <hi rend="italic"
                        >Staul</hi> [<hi rend="italic">St. Paul</hi>] arriving 10 a.m. was therefore
                    signalled off and failed to pick up second load of day.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 811, Department 555, Shanghai 542, Tsingtao, Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
